5:
Lilie, am I allowed to process these
papers?
9:
Oh, those? Only if you don't mind
doing it.
18:
Is it just me, or have you been
happier lately?
24:
If I look a little hyped, it's because it's
almost Halloween.
28:
Ah, right... There's a lot of people
curious about Palpebran Halloween,
huh?
33:
That would explain why I've been
seeing a ton of Shibuyans in
Palpebra the past couple days.
38:
Ever since Magia Fest happened,
everyone's been getting to know
each other better. With the way
things are going—
42:
Naw, you don't know what the hell
you're talkin' about!
45:
Halloween ain't Halloween without
vampire costumes!
47:
Huh? You're delusional! It's
pumpkin-themed witches that set
the mood!
53:
Ugh, you do realize no one wants to
hear old people nerding out over
cosplay, right? Take that crap
outside.
56:
Give 'em a break, Hikawa. They're
just messing around. Anyhoo, could
you show me the details of that
request you were talking about?
63:
...Looks like she's come a long way
since she first started working here.
67:
She really has. Her way with words
could use some work, but... her work
ethic's top notch.
70:
This stuff's easy to pick up when
you've got brains like I do.
74:
Hehehe, you've definitely done a lot
for us, which reminds me... I've got a
present for you!
80: ...Lilie, are you for real? Isn't this...
84:
The official Guild uniform? But with
those cat ears and tail... Is this just
cosplay?
89:
You've got it. Hikawa's not a
full-fledged member of the Guild, so
this is the best I can do.
93:
It's perfect for Halloween though,
don't you think?
103: ...Of course I do. I always look cute.
106:
Still, it's nice to dress up for the
occasion.
116:
I'm glad to hear you like it. Now, are
you ready to work your butt off for
the next few days?
124:
The Guild manages a lot of
festivities for Halloween, you know?
We need all hands on deck to make
sure everything goes smoothly.
135:
*sigh* No one told me there'd be this
much work... It never ends...
142:
Oh. Ooooh. I remember you from my
Aegis days. Satomi, right? Been a
while.
145:
Guess the rumors were true.
Judging by that outfit, you're
actually working at the Guild...
148:
Yeah, and? I know how to get stuff
done, and they needed the help.
151:
...There you go again, acting like
you're that much better than the
rest of us when you're just a poser.
157:
Pfft, sounds like someone's jealous.
Don't tell me you're still stuck
fighting with those other cocky brats.
160:
Not that I expected anything
different. Losers like you don't
change that easy—
163:
Tch... What am I running my mouth
for, when I...
166:
*sigh* Forget this, I'm done here.
Good luck with whatever it is you're
up to. See ya.
172:
What, you want more? I'm seriously
busy with work right now—which you
probably don't believe, but whatever.
175:
...Sorry, I shouldn't have lashed out
like that. I was out of line.
177:
The thing is... I've got something to
ask you...
183:
So this Satomi wants to be put
under the Guild's protection?
187:
...I mean, potentially. She's not sure
about it yet, but she'll let us know
when she decides.
191:
Understood. We should prepare the
paperwork ahead of time so the
process can go smoothly.
195:
...Why bother? We're already up to
our eyes in work, and there's no
guarantee she'll end up coming
here anyway.
199:
Hikawa, what do you think about
making your uniform official?
207:
How about it? Want to become a
full-fledged Adventurer's Guild staff
member?
211:
Y-you can't be serious. You know
I'm... I...
216:
You've changed—more than you
realize. In my humble opinion, you're
more than fit for the job.
224:
You don't have to give me an
answer right away. It's a big
decision, so take your time mulling it
over.
228:
...Fine, I'll give it some serious
thought.
236:
Say, why don't you prepare all of
Satomi's papers alone? It'll make for
some good training.
240:
There's also a ton of other things we
should cover to prepare you for
being a receptionist!
245:
W-wait, I won't have any time to
enjoy Halloween if I have to do all
that!
249:
Don't worry, we Guild receptionists
have our own way of enjoying the
festivities! Now let's get down to
business!
253: Y-your idea of fun is messed up!
257:
I think I'll pass on being a
full-fledged member, thanks!
